      "id": "r1",
      "order": 0,
      "text": "In the Englishman Joseph Priestley, the discoverer of oxygen, made a most important experiment. He knew from experience that air is necessary to plants and ani- mals. He knew that if you put a live mouse, for example, under a glass so that no fresh air can come to it, the mouse in a short time will die. It will have taken all the oxygen out of the air and without oxygen it cannot go on living.",
